ivardefs.name: amount
ivardefs.desc: Used to capture quantitative values for a variety of elements. If only limits are given, the arithmetic mean would be the average. If only a single definite value for a given element is given, it would be captured in this field.

ivardefs.name: method
ivardefs.desc: The method by which the molecular weight was determined.

ivardefs.name: type
ivardefs.desc: Type of molecular weight such as exact, average (also known as. number average), weight average.

properties.desc: The molecular weight or weight range (for proteins, polymers or nucleic acids).
